## Why This Is Asked

Tests ability to implement runtime tenant isolation in a lightweight way, showing practical use of JWT claims, middleware, IAM, and CI rollback without redesigning data stores.

## Key Concepts

- JWT tenant_id validation
- Cloud Endpoints + IAP gating
- Cloud Run service account with least privilege
- IAM Conditions to enforce per-tenant access
- CI testing with synthetic tenants and rollback

## Code Example

```javascript
// Minimal example: Express middleware validates tenant_id in JWT
async function tenantMiddleware(req, res, next) {
  const tenant = req.user?.tenant_id;
  const allowed = new Set((process.env.ALLOWED_TENANTS || '').split(',').filter(Boolean));
  if (!tenant || !allowed.has(tenant)) return res.status(403).send('Forbidden');
  req.tenant = tenant;
  next();
}
```

